recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2000-2005 323iT, 325iT, 325xiT, 320i, 323i, 325i, 325xi, 328i, 330i and 330xi and 2000-2006 323Ci, 325Ci, 328Ci, 330Ci, M3 Coupe, 323Cic, 325Cic, 330Cic, and M3 Convertible vehicles equipped with non-desiccated frontal Takata PSAN inflators and PSPI passenger frontal air bag inflators containing phase stabilized ammonium nitrate (PSAN) propellant that were used as interim remedy parts for previous Takata recalls.  These inflators may explode due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to high absolute humidity, high temperatures, and high temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: An inflator explosion may result in sharp metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: BMW will notify owners, and dealers will replace the passenger's front air bag, free of charge.  The recall began February 13, 2020.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain 2000-2002 BMW 320i, 323i, 325i, 325xi, 330i, 330xi, 323Ci, 325Ci, 330Ci, M3, 323iT, 325iT and 325xiT vehicles, 2001-2002 525i, 530i, 540i, M5, 525iT and 540iT vehicles, and 2001-2003 X5 3.0i, X5 4.4i, and X5 4.6is vehicles.  These vehicles may have had a driver-side air bag module installed as replacement equipment such as after a vehicle crash necessitating replacement of the original air bag, or as a remedy part for a prior recall.  These replacement modules contain an air bag inflator that may rupture due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to lower absolute humidity, temperature and temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: In the event of a crash necessitating deployment of the driver's frontal air bag, the inflator could rupture with metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised not to drive their vehicles until the vehicle has been remedied.  BMW will notify owners, and dealers will inspect the driver side air bag module, replacing it as necessary, free of charge.  The recall began March 15, 2017.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: BMW of North America, LLC (BMW) is recalling certain model year 2000 323i sedans, coupes, convertibles, and Sports Wagons; 2000 328i sedans and coupes; 2001-2005 325i sedans, coupes, convertibles, and Sport Wagons; 2001-2005 325xi sedans and Sports Wagons; 2006 325i coupes and convertibles; 2001-2006 330i sedans, coupes, and convertibles; 2001-2005 330xi sedans; and 2001-2006 M3 coupes and convertibles to address a safety defect in the passenger side frontal air bag which may produce excessive internal pressure that could cause the air bag inflator to rupture upon deployment of the air bag.
recalls.Consequence: In the event of a crash necessitating deployment of the passenger's frontal air bag, excessive internal pressure could cause rupturing of the inflator resulting in metal fragments striking and potentially seriously injuring the passenger seat occupant or other occupants.
recalls.Remedy: Owners are advised not to drive their vehicles until they have been repaired. BMW will notify owners, and dealers will replace the passenger side frontal air bag, free of charge.  An interim notice was mailed to owners in September 2014.  A second notice was mailed when an adequate supply of parts became available, on December 1, 2014.  Owners may contact BMW customer service at 1-800-525-7417 or email BMW at CustomerRelations@bmwusa.com.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.  This is an expansion of NHTSA Recall 13V-172.

recalls.Summary: VEHICLE DESCRIPTION:   PASSENGER VEHICLES.  THE TWO SCREWS THAT SECURE THE PARKING BRAKE CABLE MOUNTING BRACKET TO THE BACKING PLATE WERE NOT TIGHTENED PROPERLY.  AS A RESULT, THE SCREWS COULD LOOSEN AND EVENTUALLY FALL INTO THE PARKING BRAKE DRUM.
recalls.Consequence: IF THIS WERE TO HAPPEN, THE CABLE MOUNTING BRACKET WOULD NO LONGER BE FIXED TO THE BACKING PLATE AND THE PARKING BRAKE COULD NO LONGER BE APPLIED ON THAT SIDE OF THE VEHICLE.  IT IS ALSO POSSIBLE THAT A SCREW COULD LODGE WITHIN THE PARKING BRAKE DRUM, IMPAIRING THE FREE MOVEMENT OF THE DRUM.  THIS WOULD PRODUCE NOISE, AND COULD CAUSE THE PARKING BRAKE ON THAT SIDE TO LOCK UP WHILE DRIVING.
recalls.Remedy: DEALERS WILL REPLACE THE PARKING BRAKE CABLE ATTACHING SCREWS AND SECURE THEM WITH THE PROPER TORQUE.  OWNER NOTIFICATION BEGAN OCTOBER 4, 2001.   OWNERS WHO TAKE THEIR VEHICLES TO AN AUTHORIZED DEALER ON AN AGREED UPON SERVICE DATE AND DO NOT RECEIVE THE FREE REMEDY WITHIN A REASONABLE TIME SHOULD CONTACT BMW AT 1-800-831-1117.
recalls.Notes: ALSO CONTACT THE NATIONAL HIGHWAY TRAFFIC SAFETY ADMINISTRATION'S AUTO SAFETY HOTLINE AT 1-888-DASH-2-DOT (1-888-327-4236).

issues.title: VANOS System Failure
issues.description: The Variable Valve Timing (VANOS) system commonly fails due to worn seals and solenoids, causing poor engine performance and timing issues
issues.fix_description: Replace VANOS seals, solenoids, and potentially the entire VANOS unit. Use updated parts from BMW
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid extended oil change intervals

issues.title: Subframe Cracking
issues.description: Rear subframe mounting points crack due to stress and corrosion, potentially causing catastrophic handling issues
issues.fix_description: Weld reinforcement plates or replace entire subframe assembly with reinforced version
issues.prevention: Regular inspection of subframe area, avoid road salt exposure when possible

issues.title: Rod Bearing Failure
issues.description: Engine rod bearings wear prematurely, leading to complete engine failure if not addressed
issues.fix_description: Complete engine rebuild or replacement with updated bearings and proper clearances
issues.prevention: Frequent oil analysis, quality oil and filters, avoid high RPM when engine is cold

issues.title: Cooling System Expansion Tank Failure
issues.description: Plastic expansion tank develops cracks leading to coolant loss and potential overheating
issues.fix_description: Replace expansion tank with updated version, flush cooling system
issues.prevention: Regular cooling system maintenance, avoid overpressurization

issues.title: SMG Pump Failure
issues.description: Sequential Manual Gearbox hydraulic pump fails, causing transmission to get stuck in gear
issues.fix_description: Replace SMG hydraulic pump and accumulator, reprogram transmission control unit
issues.prevention: Regular SMG service, avoid aggressive shifting patterns

issues.title: Window Regulator Failure
issues.description: Power window regulators fail causing windows to drop or become inoperable
symptoms: window won't go up or down
issues.fix_description: Replace window regulator motor and mechanism
issues.prevention: Avoid forcing windows when they show signs of slow operation

issues.title: Fuel Pump Failure
issues.description: In-tank fuel pump fails causing fuel starvation and stalling, especially under high performance driving
issues.fix_description: Replace fuel pump assembly, clean fuel tank if contaminated
issues.prevention: Keep fuel tank at least 1/4 full, use quality fuel, replace fuel filter regularly

issues.title: Clutch Disc Wear (Manual Transmission)
issues.description: Clutch disc wears prematurely due to aggressive driving and high torque output
issues.fix_description: Replace clutch disc, pressure plate, release bearing, and resurface flywheel
issues.prevention: Avoid riding the clutch, proper shifting technique, avoid burnouts

issues.title: Air Mass Meter (MAF) Failure
issues.description: Mass airflow sensor fails causing incorrect air/fuel mixture and poor engine performance
issues.fix_description: Replace mass airflow sensor with OEM unit, clean air intake system
issues.prevention: Use quality air filters, avoid aftermarket intake modifications

issues.title: Differential Mounting Bushing Failure
issues.description: Rear differential mounting bushings deteriorate causing vibration and drivetrain noise
issues.fix_description: Replace differential mounting bushings with updated parts
issues.prevention: Avoid hard launches, regular drivetrain inspection

issues.title: Brake Pad Wear and Rotor Warping
issues.description: High performance braking system experiences rapid pad wear and rotor warping under aggressive use
issues.fix_description: Replace brake pads and rotors, upgrade to performance pads for track use
issues.prevention: Proper brake bedding procedure, avoid overheating brakes, quality brake fluid

issues.title: Control Arm Bushing Deterioration
issues.description: Front and rear control arm bushings wear out causing poor handling and alignment issues
issues.fix_description: Replace worn control arm bushings or entire control arms
issues.prevention: Regular suspension inspection, avoid potholes when possible

editorial.tagline: The last naturally aspirated M3 masterpiece
editorial.hero_blurb: The E46 M3 represents BMW M's final love letter to naturally aspirated performance. With its screaming S54 inline-six and perfectly balanced chassis, it's the purest expression of what made M cars legendary.
editorial.essence: This is the M3 that enthusiasts consider the holy grail - a perfect storm of lightweight construction, naturally aspirated power, and sublime chassis balance. The S54 engine's 8,000 RPM redline and the car's analog feedback represent the end of an era before turbos and electronic aids took over.
editorial.heritage: Building on the E36 M3's success, the E46 generation refined the formula with increased rigidity, more sophisticated suspension, and the brand-new S54 engine. It was BMW M's answer to the growing competition from AMG and Audi RS models.
editorial.design_philosophy: Engineers prioritized pure driving experience over outright speed, creating a car that rewards skill and involvement. Every component was developed to deliver maximum feedback and connection between driver and machine.
editorial.motorsport_history: Dominated touring car racing worldwide and served as the basis for the legendary M3 GTR. The road car's racing DNA is evident in every component, from the carbon fiber roof to the motorsport-derived S54 engine.
editorial.engine_character: The S54 is a high-strung thoroughbred that comes alive above 4,000 RPM, delivering a linear, intoxicating rush to its 8,000 RPM redline. It demands to be worked hard and rewards with an addictive mechanical symphony.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 6-speed manual is mechanical perfection - precise, notchy, and deeply satisfying. Each shift feels like operating a fine Swiss watch, with perfectly weighted throws and crisp engagement.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Telepathic balance defines the E46's character. The chassis rotates beautifully on throttle, allowing skilled drivers to adjust the car's attitude with minute throttle inputs while maintaining composure and predictability.
editorial.steering_feel: Hydraulic steering delivers pure, unfiltered communication from the front wheels. It's properly weighted with zero artificial assistance, providing intimate feedback about grip levels and surface conditions.
editorial.brake_confidence: Massive Brembo brakes provide fade-resistant stopping power with excellent pedal feel. The system inspires confidence on track while remaining civilized for street use.
editorial.sound_signature: The S54's naturally aspirated wail builds from a purposeful growl to a spine-tingling scream at redline. The exhaust note is mechanical music - raw, honest, and utterly addictive.
editorial.ideal_owner: Driving purists who prioritize engagement over convenience, track day enthusiasts who appreciate analog feedback, and collectors who recognize this as the end of an era.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Daily commuters seeking luxury comfort, those wanting modern tech features, or drivers who prefer effortless low-end torque over high-rev thrills.
editorial.buyers_summary: Prices are climbing as enthusiasts recognize the E46 M3's significance as the last analog M car. Look for well-maintained examples with service history, as the S54 requires dedicated care. This is your last chance to own M3 perfection before they become museum pieces.

expertReviews.title: Why I fell in love again with the BMW E46 M3
pros: Classic BMW design with double headlamps and perfect proportions
S54 3.2L naturally aspirated engine with 8000 RPM redline and amazing sound
Excellent hydraulic steering with great feedback and precision
Perfect 50/50 weight distribution and lightweight at 3300 lbs
Six-speed manual transmission with precise shifts
Strong connection between driver and car with analog feel
Good daily driver potential while still being track capable
Better value proposition compared to E92 M3
cons: Clutch feels heavy compared to newer BMW M cars
Car rattles quite a bit
Interior shows age with 66,000 miles
Small kidney grilles may look outdated to some
expertReviews.verdict: The E46 M3 represents the perfect balance of classic BMW design, analog driving experience, and modern usability. With its naturally aspirated S54 engine, hydraulic steering, and 50/50 weight distribution, it offers an unmatched connection between driver and car that newer BMWs lack. The reviewer considers it one of the best M3s ever made and predicts it will appreciate in value as a future classic.

expertReviews.title: Why the BMW M3 E46 is Near-Perfect (and Still Relevant)
pros: Perfect 50/50 weight distribution
3.2L inline-6 engine revs to 8000 RPM
Beautiful design with perfect proportions
343 horsepower in lightweight 1450kg chassis
6-speed manual faster than SMG (5.1s vs 5.2s)
Excellent steering feel and cornering ability
Top speed of 290 kph
Timeless styling that looks great 20 years later
cons: Would benefit from modern suspension upgrades
Needs new tires to feel fully modern
Could use performance modifications to maximize potential
expertReviews.verdict: The reviewer considers the E46 M3 'the perfect M car' and one of the greatest driver's cars ever made. Despite being 20 years old, it remains relevant with its naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-6, perfect weight distribution, and timeless design. The reviewer expresses genuine excitement and regret for not considering buying one earlier, calling it 'everything a man desires' in a sports car.

expertReviews.title: The E46 BMW M3 Is an Analog, Old-School Future Classic
pros: Analog, old-school driving experience with manual transmission
High-quality interior materials and excellent button/control feel
First North American M3 with full European power (333 hp)
Subtle, restrained exterior design - 'you have to know to know'
Interesting quirky features like variable redline and coin storage
Large trunk space despite being a coupe
Expected to become an iconic future classic
cons: SMG sequential transmission developed reputation for being clunky and unreliable
Small, cramped back seat
Cost-cutting measures evident in blank switches and panels
No rear window controls for back seat passengers
Limited body style options (coupe or convertible only)
expertReviews.verdict: The E46 M3 represents BMW's transition from subtle, driver-focused performance cars to the more ostentatious modern era. With its 3.2L S54 engine producing 333hp, it was finally the full-power M3 North America deserved. Doug emphasizes its analog nature, high-quality interior feel, and restrained styling that doesn't scream for attention. While it has some quirks and cost-cutting measures, it's positioned as a future classic that embodies old-school BMW M car philosophy.

expertReviews.title: Track Prepped 2002 BMW E46 M3 Review - This Is How It's Done!
pros: Natural and easy to drive
Excellent body control with Ground Control coilovers
Great throttle response
Good compliance for street use despite track setup
Impressive lap times with relatively basic mods
Light weight at 3,150 lbs
295 wheel horsepower with engine mods
cons: Very rubbery OEM shifter
Light steering with insufficient load-up in corners
Squealing brakes
Makes a lot of noise with stripped interior
Feels all bumps and reflectors more than stock
expertReviews.verdict: A well-executed track-focused E46 M3 that remains streetable. The car demonstrates that basic modifications can achieve impressive performance - lap times of 1:58 at Thunderhill East and 1:41 at Laguna Seca. While the shifter needs upgrading and steering could be more communicative, the overall package offers excellent track capability without being punishing on the street. Reviewer considers it top 2-3 choice for sub-$40k track builds.

expertReviews.title: My Review On The BMW E46 M3!
pros: Excellent handling and drifting capability
Reliable daily driver
Increasing in value as collectible
Natural aspirated engine with great sound
Manual transmission preferred by enthusiasts
Comfortable seats with good support
Direct steering and planted feel
Easy to drive fast without being overwhelming
cons: High mileage examples common due to daily use
Getting harder to find in standard condition
Prone to boot cracking issues
Wheels commonly stolen without locking nuts
SMG transmission criticized as confused
expertReviews.verdict: The E46 M3 is considered by many as the best M3 generation, offering the perfect balance of performance, reliability, and daily usability. With a naturally aspirated 3.2L inline-six producing strong torque, excellent handling, and increasing collectible value, it represents both a great driving experience and investment opportunity. The manual coupe variant is most desirable, though finding low-mileage examples is becoming increasingly difficult.

expertReviews.title: BMW E46 M3 Review | Is it Really THAT Good?!
pros: Naturally aspirated straight-6 engine with great sound and linear power delivery
Excellent steering feel and quick steering rack that makes you feel like a hero
Timeless design that doesn't look dated, best-looking M3 BMW ever made
Great value proposition for sports cars between $10-20k
Encourages high-rev driving with power band from 4000-7500 rpm
Classic BMW gauges that are perfectly positioned and functional
cons: SMG transmission has jerky shifts and requires learning curve
Lack of torque below 3500 rpm
Interior feels dated compared to modern cars
Can actually stall despite not having a clutch pedal
Would prefer manual transmission over SMG
expertReviews.verdict: The E46 M3 is a fantastic naturally aspirated sports car with timeless design, excellent steering, and encouraging high-rev character. While the SMG transmission has quirks and the interior feels dated, it represents great value in the $10-20k sports car segment. The reviewer would prefer the manual version but acknowledges this SMG example as surprisingly good.
